ASSIGNMENT 29: Electricity bill using switch-case
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input number of units consumed units
STEP 3: Using switch-case:
  - If units <= 100, calculate bill = units * 5 and print
  - Else if units <= 200, calculate bill = units * 7 and print
  - Else if units <= 1000, calculate bill = units * 10 and print
  - Default: print "Invalid input"
STEP 4: End

ASSIGNMENT 30: Check grade of a student using switch-case
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input marks marks
STEP 3: If marks < 0 or marks > 100, print "Invalid marks entered"
STEP 4: Else, divide marks by 10 and use switch-case:
  - Case 10 or 9 → If marks >= 95 → grade = "A+", else grade = "A"
  - Case 8 → grade = "B"
  - Case 7 → grade = "C"
  - Default → grade = "F"
STEP 5: Print "Your grade = grade"
STEP 6: End

ASSIGNMENT 31: Sum of N natural numbers
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input a number n
STEP 3: Initialize sum = 0
STEP 4: For i = 1 to n, add i to sum
STEP 5: Print "Sum of N natural numbers = sum"
STEP 6: End

ASSIGNMENT 32: Multiplication table of any number using for loop
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input a number n
STEP 3: For i = 1 to 10, calculate p = n * i
STEP 4: Print "n x i = p"
STEP 5: End

ASSIGNMENT 33: Factorial of a number using for loop
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input a number n
STEP 3: Initialize f = 1
STEP 4: For i = 1 to n, multiply f = f * i
STEP 5: Print "Factorial of n = f"
STEP 6: End

ASSIGNMENT 34: Fibonacci series up to N terms
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input a number n
STEP 3: Initialize a = b = 1, c = 0
STEP 4: For i = 0 to n, print c, then update:
  - a = b
  - b = c
  - c = a + b
STEP 5: End
 
ASSIGNMENT 35: Print all prime numbers in a range
ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: Start
STEP 2: Input lower limit l and upper limit h
STEP 3: For i = l to h:
  - Initialize c = 0
  - For j = 1 to i:
    - If i % j == 0, increment c
  - If c == 2, print i (prime number)
STEP 4: End
